The given Tundra code is almost correct, except that it should have parsed 
the scores to numbers before performing any arithmetic operations instead o
of adding 1 directly after parsing them. The fixed version would be like th
this:

```tundra
def buildSelected(names, scores) {
  return {
    name: names[0],
    score: parseNumber(scores[0]) + 1
  };
}

val names = ["Ada", "Bea"];
val scores = ["10", "20"];

val selected = buildSelected(names, scores);
print(selected.score); // output should be 11 instead of 21
```

In the original program, it's trying to add a string "10" with 1 which resu
results in concatenation rather than arithmetic addition. This has been cor
corrected by parsing the score as a number before performing addition. Now 
the 'selected.score' will be an actual numeric value and not just a string 
representation of its integer value, so it adds up correctly to give 21.
